Here’s a **step-by-step post-installation process** to transform your **existing Windows 11** into an **open, non-restricted system** (like Linux), **tailored for your workflow** (Affinity, DaVinci Resolve, Wacom, DXO, SilkyPix, Luminar Neo).
At the end, I’ll provide **instructions for an AI agent** (e.g., Mistral Codex, AutoHotkey, or a Python script) to **automate these steps**.

---

---

---

## **📋 Post-Installation Process for Open Windows 11**
*(For your existing Windows 11 system)*

---

### **⚠️ Prerequisites**
1. **Backup your system** using **[Macrium Reflect Free](https://www.macrium.com/reflectfree)** or **Clonezilla**.
2. **Ensure you have admin rights**.
3. **Download these tools** (save to `C:\OpenWin11`):
   - [Sycnex Windows10Debloater](https://github.com/Sycnex/Windows10Debloater) (PowerShell script)
   - [DisableWinTracking](https://github.com/10se1ucgo/DisableWinTracking) (telemetry blocker)
   - [Open-Shell](https://github.com/Open-Shell/Open-Shell-Menu/releases) (Start Menu replacement)
   - [RoundedTB](https://github.com/ramensoftware/roundtb/releases) (Taskbar customization)
   - [DDU (Display Driver Uninstaller)](https://www.guru3d.com/files-details/display-driver-uninstaller-download.html) (for clean GPU driver reinstall)

---

---
---

## **🔧 Step-by-Step Manual Process**

---

### **🔹 Step 1: Create a System Restore Point**
**Why?** Allows you to **roll back** if something breaks.
**Command:**
```powershell
Checkpoint-Computer -Description "Pre-OpenWin11-Tweaks" -RestorePointType MODIFY_SETTINGS
```

---

### **🔹 Step 2: Clean Up Existing Drivers (Optional but Recommended)**
**Why?** Ensures **no conflicts** with new tweaks.
1. Download **[DDU](https://www.guru3d.com/files-details/display-driver-uninstaller-download.html)**.
2. **Boot into Safe Mode**:
   - Press `Win + R`, type `msconfig`, go to **Boot** tab, check **Safe Boot**, and reboot.
3. Run **DDU** to **remove NVIDIA/Wacom drivers**.
4. Reboot into **Normal Mode** and reinstall:
   - [NVIDIA Studio Drivers](https://www.nvidia.com/Download/driverResults.aspx/198946/)
   - [Wacom Drivers](https://www.wacom.com/en-us/support/product-support/drivers)

---

### **🔹 Step 3: Debloat Windows 11**
**Tool:** [Sycnex/Windows10Debloater](https://github.com/Sycnex/Windows10Debloater)
**Why?** Removes **bloatware, telemetry, and unnecessary services** while preserving **GPU/Wacom/licensing**.

**Steps:**
1. Open **PowerShell as Administrator**.
2. Run:
   ```powershell
   Set-ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Scope Process -Force
   Invoke-Expression ((New-Object System.Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Sycnex/Windows10Debloater/master/Windows10Debloater.ps1'))
   ```
3. Select **Option 1: Remove All Bloat**.
4. **Do NOT disable** these services (critical for your workflow):
   - `NvContainerLocalSystem` (NVIDIA GPU)
   - `TabletInputService` (Wacom)
   - `CryptSvc` (Licensing for Affinity/DXO)
   - `Winmgmt` (Driver management)
   - `Audiosrv` (Audio for DaVinci Resolve)

---

### **🔹 Step 4: Disable Telemetry and Tracking**
**Tool:** [DisableWinTracking](https://github.com/10se1ucgo/DisableWinTracking)
**Why?** Blocks **Microsoft’s data collection**.

**Steps:**
1. Download and run **[DisableWinTracking](https://github.com/10se1ucgo/DisableWinTracking)**.
2. **Manually block telemetry domains** in `C:\Windows\System32\drivers\etc\hosts`:
   ```text
   127.0.0.1 telemetry.microsoft.com
   127.0.0.1 vortex.data.microsoft.com
   127.0.0.1 settings-sandbox.data.microsoft.com
   127.0.0.1 wns.notify.windows.com
   127.0.0.1 reports.wes.df.telemetry.microsoft.com
   127.0.0.1 services.wes.df.telemetry.microsoft.com
   127.0.0.1 sqm.telemetry.microsoft.com
   127.0.0.1 oca.telemetry.microsoft.com
   ```

---

### **🔹 Step 5: Disable Forced Updates**
**Why?** Prevents **Windows from reinstalling bloat or breaking drivers**.
**Method 1: Group Policy (Recommended)**
1. Press `Win + R`, type `gpedit.msc`, and hit **Enter**.
2. Navigate to:
   **Computer Configuration > Administrative Templates > Windows Components > Windows Update**
3. Enable:
   - **Configure Automatic Updates** > Set to **Disabled**.

**Method 2: Registry (If No Group Policy)**
1. Open **Regedit** (`Win + R` > `regedit`).
2. Navigate to:
   ```
   HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\WindowsUpdate
   ```
3. Create these **DWORD (32-bit) Values**:
   | **Name** | **Value** |
   |----------|----------|
   | `SetUpdateNotificationLevel` | `1` |
   | `DoNotConnectToWindowsUpdateInternetLocations` | `1` |
   | `DeferFeatureUpdatesPeriodInDays` | `365` |
   | `DeferQualityUpdatesPeriodInDays` | `365` |

**Method 3: Stop Windows Update Service**
```cmd
sc stop wuauserv
sc config wuauserv start= disabled
sc stop UsoSvc
sc config UsoSvc start= disabled
```
⚠️ **Warning:** **Manually update NVIDIA/Wacom drivers** from their official websites.

---

### **🔹 Step 6: Disable Unnecessary Services**
**Why?** Frees up **system resources** and reduces background activity.
**Safe to Disable:**
```cmd
sc stop DiagTrack && sc config DiagTrack start= disabled
sc stop dmwappushservice && sc config dmwappushservice start= disabled
sc stop WSearch && sc config WSearch start= disabled
sc stop SysMain && sc config SysMain start= disabled
sc stop WerSvc && sc config WerSvc start= disabled
```

**❌ Do NOT Disable (Critical for Your Workflow):**
- `NvContainerLocalSystem` (NVIDIA)
- `TabletInputService` (Wacom)
- `CryptSvc` (Licensing)
- `Winmgmt` (Driver Management)
- `Audiosrv` (Audio)

---

### **🔹 Step 7: Disable Scheduled Tasks**
**Why?** Stops **background tasks** that reinstall bloat or collect data.
**Tasks to Disable:**
```powershell
$Tasks = @(
    "Microsoft\Windows\Application Experience\Microsoft Compatibility Appraiser",
    "Microsoft\Windows\Application Experience\ProgramDataUpdater",
    "Microsoft\Windows\Autochk\Proxy",
    "Microsoft\Windows\Customer Experience Improvement Program\Consolidator",
    "Microsoft\Windows\DataIntegrityScan\DataIntegrity",
    "Microsoft\Windows\DiskDiagnostic\Microsoft-Windows-DiskDiagnosticDataCollector",
    "Microsoft\Windows\WindowsUpdate\Scheduled Start"
)
foreach ($Task in $Tasks) {
    Disable-ScheduledTask -TaskName $Task -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
}
```

---

### **🔹 Step 8: Allow Unsigned Drivers (For Wacom/Capture Card)**
**Why?** Enables **custom or unsigned drivers** (e.g., for Wacom or capture cards).
**Method: Test Mode (Recommended)**
```cmd
bcdedit /set testsigning on
```
- **Reboot** to apply. Your system will show a **"Test Mode"** watermark.
- **To revert**: `bcdedit /set testsigning off`

---

### **🔹 Step 9: Customize the UI (Like Linux)**
#### **1. Replace Start Menu with Open-Shell**
1. Download and install **[Open-Shell](https://github.com/Open-Shell/Open-Shell-Menu/releases)**.
2. Set as default Start Menu in **Open-Shell settings**.

#### **2. Customize Taskbar with RoundedTB**
1. Download and install **[RoundedTB](https://github.com/ramensoftware/roundtb/releases)**.
2. Configure in **RoundedTB settings** (e.g., center taskbar, rounded corners).

#### **3. Enable Large Text**
1. Open **Settings > Ease of Access > Display**.
2. Set **Text size** to **200%**.
3. Enable **Bold text**.

#### **4. Disable Animations**
1. Open **System Properties** (`sysdm.cpl`).
2. Go to **Advanced > Performance Settings**.
3. Select **Adjust for best performance** > **Apply**.

---

### **🔹 Step 10: Install Package Managers (Like Linux)**
**Why?** Easily install and manage software via CLI.
**Options:**
| **Tool** | **Install Command** | **Example Usage** |
|----------|---------------------|-------------------|
| **Winget** | Built into Windows 11 | `winget install Notepad++.Notepad++` |
| **Scoop** | `Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser; irm get.scoop.sh | iex` | `scoop install git python` |
| **Chocolatey** | `Set-ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Scope Process -Force; [System.Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol = [System.Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol -bor 3072; iex ((New-Object System.Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://community.chocolatey.org/install.ps1'))` | `choco install ffmpeg` |

---

### **🔹 Step 11: Install WSL2 for Linux Tools (Optional)**
**Why?** Run **Linux tools** (e.g., Python, Mistral API, TinyLlama) alongside Windows.
**Steps:**
1. Enable WSL2:
   ```powershell
   wsl --install
   ```
2. Install **Arch Linux** (or your preferred distro):
   ```powershell
   wsl --install -d Arch
   ```
3. Use WSL2 for:
   - Python automation (e.g., `pip install mistralai`).
   - Linux CLI tools (e.g., `ffmpeg`, `imagemagick`).

---

### **🔹 Step 12: Verify Your Open Windows 11 System**
**Test each of your critical apps:**
| **Software** | **Test** | **Expected Result** |
|--------------|----------|---------------------|
| **DaVinci Resolve** | CUDA acceleration | GPU rendering works |
| **Affinity Suite** | Hardware acceleration | No lag, full functionality |
| **Wacom Tablet** | Pen pressure/tilt | Works in Affinity/SilkyPix |
| **DXO/Luminar Neo** | Licensing | No activation errors |
| **NVIDIA Drivers** | Control Panel | Latest Studio Drivers installed |
| **Capture Card** | Recording | Works with third-party software |
| **Windows Updates** | Settings > Update | No forced updates |

